---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Web Hosting – Onyx Labs"
  description="Hosting tuned for AI workloads."
>
  <section class="content-main">
    <div class="container shell">
      <div class="content-layout">
        <div>
          <div class="content-kicker">Web Hosting</div>
          <h1 class="content-heading">Hosting tuned for AI workloads.</h1>
          <p class="content-lede">
            We design and manage hosting setups for AI-intensive applications with opinionated
            defaults around performance, security, and observability.
          </p>
          <div class="content-tags">
            <span class="tag">Managed Hosting</span>
            <span class="tag">Security & Compliance</span>
            <span class="tag">Monitoring</span>
            <span class="tag">Incident Response</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <aside class="content-panel">
          <h3>Focus areas</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Secure configuration of cloud and edge providers.</li>
            <li>Latency and cost optimization for model calls.</li>
            <li>End-to-end logging and tracing of AI flows.</li>
            <li>Runbooks and on-call practices tailored to AI.</li>
          </ul>
        </aside>
      </div>

      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="content-panel">
          <h3>Production-ready environments</h3>
          <p>
            We configure and manage the environments your AI applications run in, from staging to
            production, with sensible defaults and clear documentation.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Infrastructure-as-code for reproducible environments.</li>
            <li>Secrets, keys, and access handled securely.</li>
            <li>Scalable hosting tuned to your traffic patterns.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="content-panel">
          <h3>Observability & operations</h3>
          <p>
            AI systems fail in new ways. We design observability that surfaces the right signals
            and workflows to respond quickly.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Metrics and dashboards for AI performance and cost.</li>
            <li>Error tracking and tracing across services.</li>
            <li>Incident response runbooks and escalation paths.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div>
            <div class="section-title">Service options</div>
            <p class="section-subtitle">
              We can help you get to launch, or stay alongside you as your AI workloads grow.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card-grid">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-label">Launch</div>
            <div class="card-title">Go-live preparation</div>
            <p class="card-body-text">
              Review and harden your hosting setup ahead of a major AI launch, with load and
              failure testing.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-label">Operate</div>
            <div class="card-title">Managed hosting</div>
            <p class="card-body-text">
              Ongoing management and monitoring of your AI application hosting environments.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-label">Optimize</div>
            <div class="card-title">Performance & cost tuning</div>
            <p class="card-body-text">
              Iterative improvements to latency, reliability, and cost as usage and models evolve.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
